-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Statoil, Vestas Wind Systems 
-- 
-- Mon Jun 16, 2014 12:45AM EDT
-- None



June 16 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Statoil and Vestas Wind Systems, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Statoil <STL.OL>: Jefferies starts with underperform; price target Nok 160 * Vestas Wind Systems <VWS.CO>: Barclays revises rating to underweight from equal weightFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.* Bavarian Nordic <BAVA.CO>: Jefferies raises target to Dkk 150 from Dkk 130; rating buy * DNB <DNB.OL>: Citigroup raises target price to Nok 140 from Nok 120; rating buy  * Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI>: RBC raises target to 2.80 euros from 2.60 euros; outperform  * Kering <PRTP.PA>: Nomura adds to European recommended portfolio  * LVMH <LVMH.PA>: Nomura adds to European recommended portfolio * Statoil <STL.OL>: Jefferies starts with underperform; price target Nok 160 * Vestas Wind Systems <VWS.CO>: Barclays revises rating to underweight from equal weight